feedback: No issues with the survey.  The questions became rather redundant but nothing worse than any other survey
task was long, the form was a bit slow for each entry

I sometimes rated seemingly similar pairs differently and I'm not sure why. It wasn't a mistake or that I wasn't paying attention, it's just that sometimes things about risks with money/sex/sports felt similar to me and sometimes they didn't. I don't have an explanation for why it was different at different times other than it just felt different. I didn't want you to read my results and think I was messing around or not paying attention, I just genuinely felt different about the pairings at different times and my answers will reflect that. Also, have a great day!
The study was a little bit confusing.

Everything worked fine.
It is quite long and repetitive. I think a little higher pay would be welcome for the time and effort required.
Thanks.
There were quite a few typos. Thanks for letting me participate.

I rather liked being able to split up my time working on the hit. I would have found it helpful to have a few examples just to set the scale, this would have been especially helpful when I first started the ratings.
The white background was annoying on the eyes given the length of the study. Details on rating guidelines might help there be less uncertainty in ratings.
N/A, all good. Thanks for the working counter at the top. Some people don't do that and it feels nightmarish.
I think more topics would be nice. Everything being about risk got pretty boring after a while.
Perhaps just my cynicism from my experience working on the Mturk platform, but that seemed like more than 200 statements and although I didn't check the clock, longer than 30 minutes.

It was all clear enough.

I think I would have liked a question counter (like 42/200) instead of / along side of the progress bar, but that's an EXTREMELY minor quibble.

It was interesting to see how context had a little influence on my comparison of the two statements - what I'd seen before, how long I'd been comparing. Interesting.

I did have a technical glitch - after #13, the site would not load the next screen. Error message was:

This site can't be reached
exp.renatofrey.net refused to connect.
ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED

After debating, I did what you said not to (no choice) and refreshed. A statement page came up, but there were no statements in the boxes. Now what? I used the email link to load the survey in a new window. I logged in, then got the last two screens of instructions before the statements. Next came a statement page with statements, and the progress bar looked right for 13. I figured maybe I didn't miss anything, and continued to the end. I counted 210 statements, so I'm hoping I didn't get any dropouts. I did the HIT with attention and sincerity throughout. I have a screengrab of the error screen if you need it for confirmation.

Thanks for inviting me! :)
I would have liked a number counter versus just a filled in bar.

Interesting :)  Thanks for inviting me to participate; I enjoyed it.

Good luck with your data collection.
Maybe make it go to the next set of statements automatically after choosing one. That could speed it up. Otherwise, it was good!
No, a few of the statements weren't 100% clear though.
nothing at all, thought it was a very cool HIT
Thank you for letting me take a part of your survey. All the best!
No technical difficulties. Nothing unclear. I liked that there was a progress bar. I was worried I would run out of time before I completed the ratings, but I finished in time.
It was a lot of things to rate in a row, was it really necessary to have that many?
I like the way you had it set up to take a break, thank you for that!
All the part of the study are very clear and easy to understand. And the study is very interesting to do.
It was pretty long, and there were so many attention checks, maybe 10+ throughout the whole survey
This was a very interesting study. I did find myself wondering how different participants would have different interpretations of the statements. Thank you and best of luck!
Loading was slow, made it much longer. Most statements were so similar it appeared to be busy work and many were repeated over and over.
